FBIS4-35521 "drnes105_r_94001" FBIS-NES-94-105 Daily Report 31 May 1994 SOUTH ASIA India Rao Calls For Steps To Increase Trade With U.S. Rao Calls For Steps To Increase Trade With U.S. BK3105162994 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 1530 GMT 31 May 94 BK3105162994 Delhi All India Radio Network English BFN [Text] The prime minister has called for specific follow-up action with a time frame to increase bilateral trade with the United States. Talking to a delegation of the Confederation of Indian Industries which called on him in New Delhi today, Mr. Narasimha Rao said that an overall change has taken place in the Indo-U.S. business climate following his recent visit to Washington. He said the Indo-U.S. subcommission on trade should be reactivated to achieve this end. Mr. Rao pointed out that the subcommmission will provide a common forum for business planning, interaction, and progress.
